Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity six years from now.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value of an Annuity} &=\$4,400\times\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{\left(1+0.083\right)^{15}}}{0.083}
\\[10pt]
&=\$4,400\times\dfrac{0.697606013
}{0.083}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$36,981.52}
\end{aligned}$$

**Therefore, based on our calculation, the present value of the annuity is $36,981.52.**

Let's now calculate the present value.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value} &=\dfrac{\$36,981.52
}{\left(1 + 0.083\right)^{5}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$36,981.52
}{1.489849101}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$24,822.33}
\end{aligned}$$

**Hence, the value of the future payment today of $4,400 per year is $24,822.33.**
